        "text_LTmwwP": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>What is Overpronation? </strong>Overpronation, or flat feet, is a common biomechanical problem that occurs in the walking process when a person’s arch collapses upon weight bearing. This motion can cause extreme stress or inflammation on the plantar fascia, potentially causing discomfort and leading to other foot problems.<br/><br/><strong>Aetrex Overpronation Orthotics:</strong><br/>Aetrex Overpronation Orthotics are designed specifically to reduce shock, control overpronation and provide maximum comfort. These orthotics are engineered with medial posting for rearfoot control to help with overpronation.</p><p><strong>Price:</strong> Available Now for $59.95</p>",
            "text_font": "body",
